<TITLE> 100,000 litres of diesel seized </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bhola, May 22 (bdnews24.com)  RAB seized one lakh litres of diesel in Bhola while it was being unloaded from a cargo ship. RAB-8 official Maj Rashed said that the oil tanker was seized from Pangashia launch terminal in Bhola early Saturday. He said, "Twelve lorries that had lifted oil from the ship were seized. Besides, eight persons were arrested from the spot along with a Pajero." The arrested persons are Md Salauddin (26), sukani of the ship, from Charnoabad, Omar Faruque (20) of Uttar Bapta area, Billal Hossain (24) of Charshifli, Md Hannan (45) of Charnoabad, Md Seraj (20) of Charvaduria, Md Bachhu (21) of Charfashion, Md Sujan Nasir (25) of Charnoabad and Anwar Hossain of Charkhali. Major Rashed said oil was lifted into tanker Jamir Shah-4 from a diesel-carrying ship bound for Khulna from Chittagong. RAB 8 assistant director Md Zamiruddin told bdnews24.com: "The price of the seized diesel will be taka 42 lakh." He said, "Twelve lorries were waiting to carry oil." Drivers of those lorries fled the scene after realising that the elite crime busters had raided. bdnews2
